overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they described as "a little donkey." The agent began
  by thoroughly reviewing the existing visual design, identifying areas for
  improvement in color, typography, spacing, form elements, and overall visual
  interest. A new, calming sleep-themed color palette was introduced, and the
  main form layout was redesigned with decorative background elements and an
  enhanced progress indicator. The welcome screen was transformed with a hero
  section and feature cards, and all core UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and cards were polished for a more modern feel. Crucially,
  consistent styling was applied across all questionnaire sections, replacing
  generic gray boxes with more refined, themed groupings. During the review, a
  console error related to  values being passed to input components was
  identified and fixed by modifying the  component to safely handle
   values. The agent ensured all changes were lint-free and committed them
  in logical, atomic groups, resulting in a much more cohesive, professional,
  and aesthetically pleasing application.
